The cleanest approach is to add a custom (non-template) overload of `visitESTreeChildren` for `hermes::ES6ClassesTransformations` in `lib/AST/ES6Class.cpp`, which uses an explicit stack to walk the AST.

Below is a patch that adds such a function at file scope in `lib/AST/ES6Class.cpp`, and disables the recursion depth counter for this visitor (since the iterative version will not overflow).

